<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-734-252  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 734 252.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lotus  Oct 1989 v5 n10 p17(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Lotus Publishing Corporation 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>No Lotus HAL for Releases 2.2 or 3. (Lotus 1-2-3 natural languageadd-in)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    LOTS.andO;Product:   Lotus 1-2-3 2.2 (Spreadsheet software) (product specifications)Lotus 1-2-3 3.0 (Spreadsheet software) (product specifications)Lotus HAL (Computer program) (usage).andO;Topic:     SpreadsheetsNatural Language Interfaces.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NO LOTUS HAL FOR RELEASES 2.2 OR 3andM;Lotus HAL, Lotus Development Corp.'s natural-language add-in for 1-2-3Release 2.01, will not work with 1-2-3 Releases 2.2 and 3.andP;  According to aLotus spokesperson, the company has no plans at this time to rework HAL forthose programs.andP;  Lotus will continue to sell and support HAL for 1-2-3Release 2.01.andM;However, Lotus did incorporate a few of HAL's most popular features intoReleases 2.2 and 3.andP;  These included the Undo function, a file-linkingcapability, and a search-and-replace function.andM;In Releases 2.2 and 3, the Undo feature reverses the last action you took,making it easier to recover from errors.andP;  However, 1-2-3 Release 2.2accomplishes this by storing in memory a complete copy of the previous stateof the worksheet.andP;  This means that with a very large worksheet, you may nothave enough memory for both the worksheet and the copy.andP;  In this case, youcan turn off the Undo feature manually.andM;The programs' File Linking feature lets you link individual cells in oneworksheet to individual cells in other worksheets.andP;  In 1-2-3 Release 3, forexample, formulas can reference not only cells in the active worksheet butalso cells in other worksheet files.andM;The Search and Replace functions in both programs let you search formula andlabel cells for text and perform individual or global replace operations.andO;</TEXT></DOC>